summary: As for the cats themselves, Schwartz is eager to tell us that, “In order to have a cat on screen — and this is what I learned...
text: As for the cats themselves, Schwartz is eager to tell us that, “In order to have a cat on screen — and this is what I learned doing this movie — you have to have an A-team of cats who all have a specialty, so there’s like a cat that you hold, and a cat that rubs up on your leg, and a cat that will swipe at you, and a cat that’s just the face cat.”
source:

I want to know which one is Mr. T.

blog.name: rebelqueenoftheliberator
blog.title: Heroes, Misfits, Adventurers and Nerds
blog.description: In case you couldn't tell, I am indeed a HUGE nerd. I mostly love sci-fi and fantasy, though I watch a whole range of stuff from detectives to comedy, and many more upcoming (watch this space). I also read many, MANY books, and am still a gamer at heart. I have a soft spot for retro shows, especially those from the 60s and 70s. My favourite series include Doctor Who, Blake's 7, Good Omens, the MCU, Star Wars, ATLA, BTVS, FMAB, The Legend of Zelda, Star Trek, Indiana Jones, Uncharted, Randall and Hopkirk (Deceased), The Professionals, The Persuaders, Krypton and Endeavour.
